original_title: Brooklyn: St. Mark's Avenue - Albany Avenue
text:
St. Marks Avenue, at the S. E. corner of Albany Avenue, showing St. Johns Roman Catholic Chapel of St. Johns Orphan Asylum. The asylum is bounded by St. Marks, Albany, and Troy Avenues and Prospect Place.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
April, 1929

2,3: The same, at a later date.

P. L. Sperr

View 2: June 11, 1930
View 3: March 29, 1932
